description:
eucaryote.tree - newick file to evolutionary tree used in Figure 1. Phylogenetic tree of eukaryotes highlighting taxa with known telomerase RNA (TR) characteristics. The tree emphasizes the switch in RNA type observed in Hymenoptera, transitioning from the H/ACA box snoRNA characteristic of Animalia to TR types typical of ciliates and plants. For the authors' full interpretation please refer to the journal article below. 
  https://doi.org/10.1042/BCJ20240501  - Link to final version of the manuscript on publishers website&nbsp; 
  https://hdl.handle.net/11104/0363232  -&nbsp; A peer-reviewed, revised Authors Accepted Manuscript (AAM). This is not the final Version of Record (VoR). To cite this manuscript please refer to the publisher's version and cite as: Fajkus, P., &amp; Fajkus, J. (2025). Telomerase RNA evolution: a journey from plant telomeres to broader eukaryotic diversity. The Biochemical journal, 482(3), BCJ20240501. https://doi.org/10.1042/BCJ20240501 
 &nbsp;

